'''Force suppression'''<ref name="KOTOR1" /><ref name="KOTOR2" /><ref name="SWG" /> also known as '''Dampen Force''',<ref name="Crystal">''[[The Crystal Star]]''</ref> was a mind-affecting [[Force power/Legends|Force power]] that was employed by crafty [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-sensitives]]. It allowed a Force-sensitive to harness the Force to shatter the Force powers another used<ref name="KOTOR1" /> or in order to convince others that they had been cut off from the Force itself.<ref name="Dynasty of Evil">''[[Darth Bane: Dynasty of Evil]]''</ref> As such, it served to diminish an enemy's [[Force resistance]]<ref name="TOR">''[[Star Wars: The Old Republic]]''</ref> and to negate a vast range of other Force abilities, including but not limited to [[Force speed/Legends|Force speed]], [[Force valor]], [[Force barrier/Legends|Force barrier]], [[Force Enrage|Force fury]], [[Inspire]], [[Energy resistance]], and even [[Battle meditation/Legends|Battle meditation]].<ref name="KOTOR1" /><ref name="KOTOR2" /> When subjected to certain uses the victim might be unable to focus enough to touch the Force,<ref name="The Courtship of Princess Leia">''[[The Courtship of Princess Leia]]''</ref> or could not control objects bigger than molecules when affected by Dampen Force. However, it did not block use of the Force entirely and only had temporary effects, though sometimes lasting for some days.<ref name="Crystal" />

Advanced mastery of this technique was referred to as '''Force breach''' during the [[Old Sith Wars]].<ref name="KOTOR1" /><ref name="KOTOR2" /> During the [[Cold War (Galactic Republic–Sith Empire)|Cold War]], that name was instead applied to the ability to deal catastrophic damage against targets by rupturing their [[Shatterpoint/Legends|shatterpoints]].<ref name="TOR" /> [[Hethrir]] was a known user of this technique, using it to control the children he kidnapped for his [[Empire Reborn]] movement. He would often dampen the abilities of non-human "students" at critical moments to perpetuate the movement's [[Humanocentrism|humanocentric]] agenda. These unfortunates would be removed as "failures" and sold into [[Slavery/Legends|slavery]] as a source of income.<ref name="Crystal" />

==Behind the Scenes==
In ''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic]]'' and its[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic II: The Sith Lords| sequel]], the power would be first unlocked as Force Suppression before being able to be upgraded to Force Breach at level 15, the difference being Force Breach was capable of removing higher-level versions of the same Force Powers. Mechanically, it acted as a sort of "buff removing" power, canceling active Force Powers that provided benefits to the target. Powers that could cancelled included: Force Aura, Force Valor, Force Speed, Energy Resistance, Force Resistance, Battle Meditation, Force Barrier, Force Body, Fury, Inspire Followers, and their upgraded variants. <ref name="KOTOR1" /><ref name="KOTOR2" /> 

